[SIZE=4][COLOR=#e67e22]■[/COLOR] [B]Setup Guide[/B][/SIZE]

[SIZE=3][COLOR=#e67e22]Step 1 — Install[/COLOR][/SIZE]

Drop [ICODE]JExVote.jar[/ICODE] into your [ICODE]plugins/[/ICODE] folder and restart the server. JExVote generates its configuration files, an RSA keypair, and a Votifier token on first launch.

[SIZE=3][COLOR=#e67e22]Step 2 — Configure the Votifier server[/COLOR][/SIZE]

Open [ICODE]config.yml[/ICODE] and check the [ICODE]votifier[/ICODE] section:

[CODE=YAML]
votifier:
  host: ''          # Leave empty to bind all interfaces
  port: 8192        # The port vote sites connect to
  token: ''         # Auto-generated on first run — copy this to your vote site settings
[/CODE]

If your host requires a specific bind address, set [ICODE]host[/ICODE] accordingly. The [ICODE]token[/ICODE] is generated automatically — copy it from the config after the first start and paste it into your vote site's Votifier settings.

[B]Important:[/B] Make sure port [ICODE]8192[/ICODE] (or whatever you set) is open in your firewall / hosting panel. Vote sites need to reach this port directly.

[SIZE=3][COLOR=#e67e22]Step 3 — Add vote sites[/COLOR][/SIZE]

Edit [ICODE]sites.yml[/ICODE] to register each voting site:

[CODE=YAML]
sites:
  serverliste:
    display-name: "Serverliste.net"
    service-name: "Serverliste"        # Must match what the site sends
    vote-url: "https://serverliste.net/vote/12345"
    cooldown-minutes: 1440             # 24-hour rolling window
    points-per-vote: 1

  mcserverlist:
    display-name: "MC Server List"
    service-name: "MCServerList"
    vote-url: "https://minecraft-server-list.com/server/12345/vote/"
    daily-reset: "00:00"              # Fixed daily reset
    timezone: "Europe/Berlin"
    points-per-vote: 2
[/CODE]

[B]Cooldown modes[/B] — pick one per site:
[LIST]
[*][ICODE]cooldown-minutes[/ICODE] — Rolling window. The player can vote again X minutes after their last vote.
[*][ICODE]daily-reset[/ICODE] + [ICODE]timezone[/ICODE] — Fixed reset. Everyone can vote again at the specified time in the given timezone.
[/LIST]

The [ICODE]service-name[/ICODE] must exactly match the service identifier that the vote site sends in its Votifier payload. If you are unsure, use [ICODE]/jexvote fakevote <player> TestService[/ICODE] or check your server log for the incoming service name.

[SIZE=3][COLOR=#e67e22]Step 4 — Configure rewards[/COLOR][/SIZE]

Open [ICODE]rewards.yml[/ICODE] to set up what players receive when they vote:

[CODE=YAML]
default-rewards:
  - type: command
    command: "give {player} diamond 1"
    as-console: true
  - type: sound
    sound: ENTITY_PLAYER_LEVELUP
    volume: 1.0
    pitch: 1.2
  - type: title
    title: "<green>Thank you!"
    subtitle: "<gray>Your vote has been counted."
    fade-in: 10
    stay: 40
    fade-out: 10
[/CODE]

Rewards are split into three categories:

[LIST]
[*][B]default-rewards[/B] — Granted on every vote, regardless of which site the vote came from.
[*][B]streak-rewards[/B] — Bonus rewards at specific streak milestones (day 7, 14, 30, etc.).
[*][B]site-rewards[/B] — Extra rewards for voting on a specific site, keyed by site ID from [ICODE]sites.yml[/ICODE].
[/LIST]

[SIZE=3][COLOR=#e67e22]Step 5 — Verify[/COLOR][/SIZE]

Use [ICODE]/jexvote fakevote <yourname>[/ICODE] to trigger a test vote and confirm that rewards, broadcasts, and the GUI all work correctly. Check the console output — JExVote logs every vote it receives with the protocol version and service name.


