[/CENTER]


[SIZE=4][COLOR=#1abc9c]■[/COLOR] [B]Configuration Reference[/B][/SIZE]

[SPOILER="config.yml — Full Reference"]
[CODE=YAML]
# ── Votifier Server ──
votifier:
  host: ''              # Bind address (empty = all interfaces)
  port: 8192            # Listener port
  token: ''             # HMAC token (auto-generated on first run)

# ── Broadcast ──
broadcast:
  mode: 'all'           # all | others | none
  cooldown: 0           # Seconds between broadcasts (0 = every vote)

# ── Private Message ──
private-message:
  enabled: true         # Send thank-you message to the voter

# ── Offline Queue ──
offline-vote-queue: true  # Deliver rewards when offline voters log in

# ── Streaks ──
streak:
  timeout-hours: 36     # Hours before a streak breaks

  # Bonus commands at streak milestones
  bonus-commands:
    7:
      - "give {player} emerald 3"
    14:
      - "give {player} diamond 1"
    30:
      - "give {player} netherite_ingot 1"

# ── Commands on Vote ──
commands-on-vote: []    # Commands executed on every vote. Placeholders: {player}, {service}, {streak}

# ── Record Retention ──
records:
  retention-days: 90    # Days to keep vote records (0 = forever)
[/CODE]
[/SPOILER]


[CENTER]
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
[/CENTER]


[SIZE=4][COLOR=#f39c12]■[/COLOR] [B]Streak System[/B][/SIZE]

Streaks track how many days in a row a player has voted. The timeout is configurable — by default, a player has 36 hours between votes before the streak resets. This gives some buffer beyond a strict 24-hour window.

Streak milestones can trigger two things independently:
[LIST]
[*][B]Bonus commands[/B] — Defined in [ICODE]config.yml[/ICODE] under [ICODE]streak.bonus-commands[/ICODE]. Quick and simple for running commands.
[*][B]Streak rewards[/B] — Defined in [ICODE]rewards.yml[/ICODE] under [ICODE]streak-rewards[/ICODE]. Uses the full reward type system (items, currency, choice menus, etc.).
[/LIST]

Both fire at the same milestone if configured. Set up whichever fits your use case — or both.

The streak progress is shown in every GUI: the overview displays a progress bar toward the next milestone, and the dedicated streak view breaks down every milestone with achieved/upcoming/locked status.


[CENTER]
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
[/CENTER]


[SIZE=4][COLOR=#2c3e50]■[/COLOR] [B]Votifier Protocol[/B][/SIZE]

JExVote includes a fully self-contained Votifier server. There is no need to install NuVotifier or any third-party listener.

[B]Supported protocols:[/B]
[LIST]
[*][B]Votifier v1[/B] — 256-byte RSA-encrypted vote block. Legacy support for older vote sites.
[*][B]NuVotifier v2[/B] — JSON payload with HMAC-SHA256 signature verification and challenge-response. Used by most modern vote sites.
[/LIST]

JExVote auto-detects the protocol version per connection. The RSA keypair is generated on first launch and stored in [ICODE]plugins/JExVote/rsa/[/ICODE]. The HMAC token is written to [ICODE]config.yml[/ICODE].

If a vote site asks for your public key, you will find it at [ICODE]plugins/JExVote/rsa/public.key[/ICODE] (Base64-encoded).


[CENTER]
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
[/CENTER]


[SIZE=4][COLOR=#16a085]■[/COLOR] [B]Language & Localization[/B][/SIZE]

JExVote ships with translations for:
[LIST]
[*][ICODE]en_US[/ICODE] — English
[*][ICODE]de_DE[/ICODE] — German
[*][ICODE]cs_CZ[/ICODE] — Czech
[*][ICODE]sk_SK[/ICODE] — Slovak
[/LIST]

The language is auto-detected per player based on their client locale. To force a specific language for the entire server, create a [ICODE]translations/config.yml[/ICODE] in the plugin folder:

[CODE=YAML]
# Force all players to see this locale regardless of client setting.
# Leave empty to use auto-detection.
force-locale: 'de_DE'
[/CODE]

You can add custom translations by placing a [ICODE]<locale>.yml[/ICODE] file in the [ICODE]translations/[/ICODE] folder. Missing keys fall back to the default English translation.


